# cz_hello — the pyfront -> Chez tracer bullet (faithful pythonic m0_hello).
#
# Pythonic source -> (pyfront) parse/lower to a faithful L2 -> (stock compiler, UNCHANGED)
# the full d3parsed_of_trans03 pipeline (incl. trans3a, which builds the t3penv) -> trxd3i0 ->
# intrep0 -> cz0emit -> Chez Scheme -> runs on Chez.  Output: 42.
#
# This is the pythonic spelling of srcgen2/xats2cz/TEST/m0_hello.dats, using the SAME prelude
# `#include`s (now via `include`).  lower_include splices the included decls into the d2parsed,
# and trans3a builds the staload t3penvs, so the prelude templates (sint_print / strn_print /
# the_print_store_log) resolve + emit through the unchanged backend.
include "prelude/HATS/prelude_dats.hats"
include "prelude/HATS/prelude_JS_dats.hats"
sint_print(42)
strn_print("\n")
the_print_store_log()
